  <span id="freeText15347034329447751822" style="display:none">Harrowing. But so informative and absorbing. Tales of heroism, tragedy, and survival fill the pages. Unlike other 9/11 accounts, this one focuses on the Trade Centers only, not on the pentagon or flight 93. Some of the account is focused on the towers themselves: the construction failures and oversights that led to needlessly trapping so many people and the towers’ inevitable collapse.<br /><br />I have an unquenchable need to understand and learn as much as I can about 9/11. I’m still trying to figure out why that is. Is it because it happened when I wash high school senior, on the cusp of adulthood myself? I don’t know. But whatever it is, and if anyone finds themselves similarly compelled, this is an indispensable account of that horrible day.</span>
